---
// "Build from source" content block — no title, no section wrapper.
// Used by /cli/install/ (inside its <section> + <h2>) and
// by the /cli/ quick-install tabs (as the "From source" panel).
---
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> go install github.com/specscore/specscore-cli/cmd/specscore@main</pre>
<p class="method-desc">
  Requires <a class="xref" href="https://go.dev/">Go</a> 1.26 or newer.
  This installs the latest development build from <code>main</code> —
  may include changes not yet in a tagged release.
</p>
<p class="method-desc">
  To pin a specific version, swap <code>@main</code> for a tag like
  <code>@v0.4.2</code>, or use <code>@latest</code> for the most recent
  tagged release.
</p>

<style>
  .method-desc {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .method-desc code {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
</style>
